{{external links|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Til Debt Do Us Part | image = | caption = | camera = | picture_format = | audio_format = | runtime = 22 minutes | creator = | developer = | producer = [[Frantic Films]] | executive_producer = | presenter = [[Gail Vaz-Oxlade]] | narrated = | opentheme = | endtheme = | country = Canada | language = English | network = [[Slice (TV channel)|Slice]] | first_aired = | last_aired = | num_episodes = | list_episodes = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | website = }} '' '''''Til Debt Do Us Part''''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] television series produced by [[Frantic Films]] for [[Slice (TV channel)|Slice]] in Canada, [[Zone Reality]] in the United Kingdom and [[AmericanLife TV Network]] and [[CNBC]] in the United States.<ref name=FinPost>{{cite news |title=Personal debt makes good reality television |url=http://www.financialpost.com/scripts/story.html?id=13566fe7-de44-459c-8467-704d13098a63&k=4993 |newspaper=Financial Post |accessdate=2010-06-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319162227/http://www.financialpost.com/scripts/story.html?id=13566fe7-de44-459c-8467-704d13098a63&k=4993 |archivedate=2012-03-19 |df= }}</ref> It is hosted by [[Gail Vaz-Oxlade]], who each week visits a couple who are in debt and having relationship troubles.<ref name=Globe>{{cite news |title=Gail Vaz-Oxlade: The accidental guru |author=Sarah Hampson |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/family-and-relationships/gail-vaz-oxlade-the-accidental-guru/article1424785/ |newspaper= The Globe and Mail |date= 2010-01-30 |accessdate=2010-06-30 }}</ref> The participants are given weekly challenges, some of which are to help bring the finances and debt under control, with the others meant to help the couple's relationship. At the end of one month, Vaz-Oxlade gives the couple a cheque for an amount up to $5,000, depending on how well they did during the challenges.<ref name=FinPost/> A [http://www.shopfranticfilms.com/products.html 52-Week Life Planner] based on the television series was released in 2013 and offers day-by-day, step-by-step strategies and tips for successfully managing household finances.
